text: Elen Yeremyan (born 27 May 2001) is an Armenian singer-songwriter who is known by her stage name Brunette. == Career == She released her first song at the age of 18 in September 2019. In 2023, she was chosen to represent Armenia at the Eurovision Song Contest 2023 with her song "Future Lover". The public voted for her to be one of the 26 finalists. At the end of the contest, Brunette finished in 14th place with 122 points. == Sources == Category:2001 births Category:Living people Category:Armenian singers Category:Eurovision Song Contest entrants
